Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:36:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] Show live prices for all market segments and fix broken
 WebSocket price stream
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Requested: show current prices for every segment in the trading terminal
(Index through Commodity) plus Top Gainers/Losers.

- market/registry.py, market/instrument.py, market/websocket.py: expand the
  default instrument universe from 4 symbols (NIFTY50, BANKNIFTY, BTCUSD,
  ETHUSD) to 17, spanning Index (NIFTY50, BANKNIFTY, FINNIFTY), Equity
  (RELIANCE, TCS, HDFCBANK, INFY, ICICIBANK, SBIN, ITC), Currency (USDINR),
  Commodity (CRUDEOIL, GOLD, SILVER, NATURALGAS), and Crypto (BTCUSD, ETHUSD).
  The mock feed, symbol registry, and instrument manager all read from the
  same symbol set, so scanners/indicators/regime pick these up automatically.

While verifying this live in a browser, found the actual reason the terminal
showed no prices at all: dashboard/main.py's ConnectionManager.broadcast()
passed event payloads straight to WebSocket.send_json(), which uses the
stdlib json encoder. Every real event payload (ticks, candles, decisions,
trades) carries nested datetime/Enum values from Pydantic's .model_dump(),
which that encoder can't serialize — so every broadcast raised inside the
bare except, silently dropped the connection from the active list, and the
client just hung with an open socket that never received anything. Fixed by
running payloads through fastapi.encoders.jsonable_encoder() before sending.
Also fixed dashboard/static/js/app.js's handleBusEvent, which passed the
outer {event_id, tick} envelope to updatePriceWidget() instead of unwrapping
tick first.

Verified live: all 17 symbols now stream prices in the terminal and Top
Gainers/Top Losers populate correctly. Added a regression test
(test_websocket_broadcast_serializes_nested_datetime) that fails without the
jsonable_encoder fix (times out, matching the real symptom) and passes with it.

